product_name: L'OrealFaux Brow Ultra Fine Double-Brush Tip Brow Filling Pen
summary: SummaryL'Oréal Paris Faux Brow Ultra Fine Double-Brush Tip Brow Filling Pen creates naturally fuller brows. Its double-brush tip effortlessly mimics brow hairs for a doubled look in one precise stroke.
details: DetailsFeaturesEffortless, hair-like brow filling pen provides natural, fuller looking browsFast and precise. Double the look of your brow hairs in one stroke with controlled applicationDouble-brush tip for quick, precise application and hair-like brow strokesUltra-thin ink for volume and shape. Lightweight and comfortable for up to 2-day wearNatural looking results. Smudge-resistant, transfer-resistant, heat-resistant, and waterproof.Key IngredientsIncludes Castor Oil to hydrate and soften eyebrow hairs.Item 2634214How To UseShake well before use. Remove cap to reveal precise, double-brush tip. Apply light handed, gentle strokes at an upward angle from the inner brow to the arch. Angle pen slightly to define the tail.Eye cosmetics in a scratched, infected or irritated eye and scratches from cosmetic eye applicators can lead to eye damage, and in extreme cases, even blindness. If your eye is scratched, stop using all eye cosmetics and go to an ophthalmologist immediately. Never apply this product in a moving vehicle.IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Acrylates/Ethylhexyl Acrylate Copolymer, Propylene Glycol, Acrylates/Dimethylaminoethyl Methacrylate Copolymer, Caprylyl Glycol, Phenoxyethanol, Ammonium Acrylates Copolymer, Sodium Laureth-12 Sulfate, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Laureth-21, C11-15 Alketh-7, Butylene Glycol, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Potassium Sorbate, Sodium Lauryl Sulfate, Disodium Laureth Sulfosuccinate. May Contain: CI 77266 [Nano] / Black 2, CI 16035 / Red 40, CI 19140 / Yellow 5]. (F.I.L. N70054215/1).
how_to_use: Shake well before use. Remove cap to reveal precise, double-brush tip. Apply light handed, gentle strokes at an upward angle from the inner brow to the arch. Angle pen slightly to define the tail.Eye cosmetics in a scratched, infected or irritated eye and scratches from cosmetic eye applicators can lead to eye damage, and in extreme cases, even blindness. If your eye is scratched, stop using all eye cosmetics and go to an ophthalmologist immediately. Never apply this product in a moving vehicle.

reviews.headline: Quick and Easy!
reviews.comments: This product easily fills out your eyebrows to natural looking fullness.

reviews.headline: New Alopecia Essential
reviews.comments: I love this pen! I had my brows done in less than 2min and they look so natural. Add the fact they don't sweat or run off lowers my anxiety and let's me walk confidently!

reviews.headline: I like it! good value for the price.
reviews.comments: Nothing bad to say. Never tried an item like this before and I'm happy with it. I'm still figuring out how I'm supposed to apply this, but it covers pretty good. I would order the next shade lighter the next time I re-order though. It covers gray well I think.

reviews.headline: Terrible
reviews.comments: Totally a gimmick. Color was terrible as well as the brush. Returned immediately.

reviews.headline: Almost perfect, leaks like crazy
reviews.comments: Thus is so close to a holy grail product. I still need to use a pencil for my brows, but the colors are spot on. Only problem—leaks like crazy. I noticed a bubble near the tip a week or less after buying. Sucks to be losing product out the side, but also when you lightly shake and then open the cap, you can sometimes get splatter to fly off which can stain clothes, ruin your makeup, or fly all over the bathroom (esp since I use dark brunette, that makes the stains extra fun). If they cpuld seal the tip better, this would be a perfect product. Also, I wondered if id just gotten a one-off and tried one from another color—same thing happened.

reviews.headline: Color range needs work
reviews.comments: Every shade pulls warm and loojs awful on me. Need neutral and cool tones to cater to all

reviews.headline: Love but defective
reviews.comments: I love the results this product gives my brows, however it seems to always leak. I thought maybe i had just one that is defective. I have now bought about 5 and each one has had the same issue. I lose so much product in the process as i have to constantly clean the excess liquid ink. Frustrating as i like the results just not sure if it's worth the waisted material.

reviews.headline: Great
reviews.comments: The brush works very well  , I pressed light  on my brown to create the shape and it looks natural  ! I won't go back to the brown pencil anymore  !

reviews.headline: Fix the cap!!!!
reviews.comments: Love the product but after a few times getting bumped in makeup tray the cap won't stay on and it dries up or leaks every where. Saw a lot of the same issues on the Loreal website. Can't recommend until they fix the cap issue.

reviews.headline: eh the package leaking needs to be fixed
reviews.comments: Sadly, this one's a miss for me. The only two pros I can give it are the great color range and the fine-tip pen, which is perfect for creating realistic hair strokes, especially if you have sparse areas that need filling in. Unfortunately, the big drawback is the constant leaking. It would seep out the sides, get all over my hands, run down the pen, and stain everything it touched. I don't usually mind a stain, but I do mind having to grab paper towels just to catch the mess, and even then, I only had a couple of seconds before it soaked through onto my hands. I thought maybe I just got a defective one, so I exchanged it at Ulta… but the replacement did the exact same thing. Sadly, the packaging design is a fail. Sorry, L'Oréal, I love a lot of your products, but this one really needs a redesign.

reviews.headline: Practice makes perfect
reviews.comments: honestly when I first bought the product I hated it. I couldn't figure it out. It sat on my desk for a while and I kept practicing and eventually I found a way to apply it to get the look I was hoping for!! its a great product for longevity but I cant use it on its own. I use a pencil to draw on my arch but the pen works beautifully to fill in the rest

reviews.headline: Not good for fine eyebrows over makeup
reviews.comments: Ive seen so many people rave about this, but it was a no for me. I got a darker color and it still would not show up. It works a little better when I apply before foundation. I much prefer the NYX brow pen.

reviews.headline: Awesome product!!
reviews.comments: I definitely will be purchasing this product again!!  I love the way this looks like natural eyebrows.  It takes some practice, but by using just a light wispy stroke to apply, it looks so much more natural than the typical filled in eyebrow pencil.

reviews.headline: My new favorite!
reviews.comments: I am in love with this brow pen. The application takes some getting used to but the size of the tip and the color is perfect to mimic brow hairs. I struggle finding the perfect blend dark brunette and this one is a perfect match. I can't attest to the waterproof aspect yet because I wash my face twice a day but it is sweat proof since I worked out immediately after applying and they didn't budge. I will be stocking up on these. Add a little eyebrow help and you're set for the day. Pro-tip if you have oily skin, pat your brows with pressed powder before applying to keep the oil at bay, that can help with longevity.

reviews.headline: Great color
reviews.comments: The tint was excellent, but it needs to stay on longer. Too easily removed. However, it has the quality and design that L'Oreal is famous for.

reviews.headline: Great product but not for me
reviews.comments: It was the perfect color but made for someone that has microblading

reviews.headline: Did not it at all.
reviews.comments: The way they promoted the information on this product was false.

reviews.headline: Best eyebrow pen ever, but the shade range…
reviews.comments: Best eyebrow pen ever, fastest eyebrow application ever, you can get easy hair like strokes, will buy it forever. Btu the only thing is the shade range, from dark bruntte to soft black is a huge jump, it would be nice to have a couple shades in between.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I recently tried the L'Oréal Paris Faux Brow, and I am *absolutely* blown away by the results. This brow product promises fuller, natural-looking brows without the need for hours of shaping and sculpting, and it delivers on that promise in every way.

**Packaging:**
The Faux Brow comes in sleek, modern packaging that's both compact and travel-friendly. The applicator is a slim, precise brush with a fine-tipped end that allows for easy control and a perfect application every time. I appreciate how the design is both functional and stylish, making it easy to hold and use.

**Formula:**
What really sets the Faux Brow apart is the lightweight, buildable formula. It's not too thick or gloopy, which means it won't leave you with a heavy, fake brow look. The product is incredibly easy to blend, which is crucial for creating a natural look. Whether you're filling in sparse areas or creating an entirely new shape, it seamlessly adheres to the brow hairs and skin without any patchiness.

**Application:**
The formula glides on effortlessly, and the brush allows for precise, controlled strokes. A little goes a long way, so you don't need to load up the applicator. For those looking to achieve a fuller, more sculpted brow, you can layer it to build more intensity without it ever looking too thick or unnatural. It's perfect for creating that feathered brow effect without any clumps. 

**Shade Range:**
The shade range is another standout feature. L'Oréal offers a variety of shades that cater to different hair colors, from light blondes to deep brunettes and black shades. The color blends beautifully with my natural brow hairs, and I've found that it doesn't look too warm or ashy—it's the perfect neutral tone for me. The formula also doesn't fade throughout the day, which is a huge win!

**Longevity:**
I was especially impressed by how well it lasted throughout the day. Even in humid conditions or after a long day at work, my brows stayed in place without smudging or fading. The product dries quickly, so there's no risk of it transferring onto your skin or smearing.

**Low to no odor**
I have a pretty sensitive sense of smell and smelled no odor whatsoever while applying this. 

**Results:**
The end result is exactly what I've been looking for: full, natural-looking brows that stay put. I love how it enhances my brows without making them look overdone. It adds volume, definition, and a subtle lift, making my eyes pop in a way that feels effortless.

**Final Thoughts:**
If you're looking for a brow product that's easy to use, long-lasting, and delivers natural, full brows, the L'Oréal Paris Faux Brow is an absolute must-try. It's affordable, effective, and works for a variety of brow types and colors. I've tried plenty of brow products in the past, but this one truly stands out. Highly recommend!
faceoff_positive.headline: Faux Brow for a Real Win!

faceoff_negative.comments: lower your expectations with this. I was hoping that FINALLY a company made one of these that worked, while it is better than others I've tried, it's still not great. If you ONLY need a few strokes at the front of the brow then sure it's great. I do like the tips and how fine they are. it's just once you've done a few strokes and try to move through the brow, the pigment just disappears. I keep trying it in different ways but it's just not good enough unfortunately. if they could take this exact tip and yet add the pigment and flowability of the NYX lift and snatch brow pen, then it would be perfect. So only buy this if you need a few hairs in the beginning. I have extremely naked brows, they were waxed to death in the early 2000s so there is very very little hair, I have to draw on and create a brow. For me the tried and true is still sigma brow powder and nyx lift and snatch pen and then some pointed qtips and a voluming tinted brow gel for the very few real nails I have. I will probably end up returning this if I can't get it to work well. I'll keep trying it a few days.
faceoff_negative.headline: it's ok
